properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 6 at 9:57PM PST until January 7 at 3:26PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warnings continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Tolt River Above Carnation affecting King County
Newaukum River Near Chehalis affecting Lewis County
Skokomish River At Potlatch affecting Mason County

Olympic Peninsula Region
Central West Region
Southwest Region

Heavy rain and snow will continue overnight into Tuesday over the area.
Snow levels will rise to near 5000 feet in the Cascades and 6000 feet
in the Olympics.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Tolt River Above Carnation
* From 3 AM Tuesday until Tuesday afternoon.
* At  8:15 PM Monday the flow was 3535 cfs.
* Flood flow is 5000 cfs.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood flow around 3 AM Tuesday
and crest near 5360 cfs around 4 AM Tuesday. The river will fall
below flood flow Tuesday morning.
* Impact...At 5000 cfs, the Tolt River will flood Tolt River Rd NE and
many driveways. Some homes in the San Souci area could be
inaccessible due to deep and quick flood waters. This river level
on the Tolt corresponds to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood
system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
